<apex:page sidebar="false" showHeader="false" applyHtmlTag="false" applyBodyTag="false" standardStylesheets="false" renderAs="pdf" controller="HIPEligibleLetterCtrl">
    <html>
    <head>
        <style type="text/css">
            @page {
                margin: 0.5in;
                size: letter;
            }
            body {
                font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
                font-size: 12pt;
                color: #000;
                line-height: 1.35;
            }
            .header {
                width: 100%;
                display: table;
                margin-bottom: 16px;
            }
            .header-left,
            .header-right {
                display: table-cell;
                vertical-align: top;
            }
            .header-right {
                text-align: right;
                width: 45%;
            }
            .date {
                margin-bottom: 6px;
            }
            .address {
                white-space: pre-line;
            }
            .header-logo {
                width: 200px;
                max-width: 100%;
                height: auto;
            }
            .re-line {
                margin: 14px 0 16px;
                font-weight: bold;
            }
            p {
                margin: 0 0 10px 0;
            }
            .section-title {
                text-align: center;
                text-decoration: underline;
                font-weight: bold;
                margin: 10px 0 8px;
            }
            .signature {
                margin-top: 16px;
            }
            .footer {
                position: fixed;
                bottom: 0.3in;
                left: 0;
                right: 0;
                text-align: center;
                font-size: 10pt;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="header">
            <div class="header-left">
                <div class="date">{!todayDate}</div>
                <div class="address">{!accountName}
{!accountAddress}</div>
            </div>
            <div class="header-right">
                <apex:image value="{!logoUrl}" rendered="{!logoUrl != null}" styleClass="header-logo"/>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="re-line">RE: Eligibility for the Home Improvement Program</div>

        <p>Dear {!accountName},</p>

        <p>
            Thank you for your interest in the Galvan Housing Resources Home Improvement
            Program. I am happy to inform you that after careful review of your application and
            supporting documentation, you have been found to be <b>eligible</b> for our program.
            Your application will be placed on our waiting list.
        </p>

        <p>
            The Home Improvement Program provides grant funds for project costs to assist
            low to moderate-income homeowners to complete necessary health and safety-
            related repairs and improvements to their homes. These grant funds will be secured
            by a note and mortgage for two to fifteen years, depending on the amount of funds,
            with <span style="text-decoration: underline;">no repayment</span> required as long as you live in and own the home for the
            specified period of time.
        </p>

        <div class="section-title">What's Next?</div>

        <p>
            Once your application has reached the top of our waiting list, our Rehab Specialist
            will notify you and arrange for an inspection of your home to discuss what repairs
            are necessary to alleviate current health and/or safety issues. A scope of work will
            be created and once approved by you, we will assemble a bid package for our pool
            of qualified, licensed contractors. After the bidding process, the lowest eligible
            bidder is chosen for the project. If the homeowner decides to select a contractor
            that is not the lowest bidder, the homeowner is responsible for contributing the
            difference between the lowest bid and the bid they select. GHR will set up a meeting
            for all contracts to be signed between the homeowner and contractor prior to the
            work being started. GHR staff will be available to you through each step of the way
            to answer any questions you may have throughout the process.
        </p>

        <p>
            We are excited to work with you and look forward to helping you make necessary
            improvements to your home! If you have any questions regarding our Home
            Improvement Program, please do not hesitate to reach out to us at (518) 822-0707.
        </p>

        <p class="signature">Sincerely,</p>
        <div>Susan Petersen</div>
        <div>Home Improvement Program Manager</div>
        <div><a href="mailto:spetersen@galvanfdn.org">spetersen@galvanfdn.org</a></div>
    </body>
    </html>
</apex:page>
